cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.CL, cs.HC

The paper analyzes chat messages from a social game-streaming platform, which involves computational text analysis methods. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including:

- cs.CY (Computers and Society): This sub-category covers topics related to the social and ethical aspects of computing, including online communities and social media.
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): This sub-category covers topics related to social networks and their analysis, which is relevant to the study of social game-streaming platforms.
- cs.SD (Software Engineering): This sub-category covers topics related to software development, which could be relevant to the development of tools for analyzing chat messages.
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): This sub-category covers topics related to natural language processing, which is relevant to the computational text analysis methods used in the paper.
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): This sub-category covers topics related to the interaction between humans and computers, which is relevant to the study of social game-streaming platforms as a social platform.
